														<div class="lotusPostDetails">
															<p>
Gang Ji,<br /><wbr>
<br /><wbr>
Yes, you can start with one machine, and expand to other machines
later. I suggest you install the "Desktop" version of Linux on your
one and only system, and then intall the applicatoins for KVM,
Libvirt, xCat, and the rest of the stack. The guest images should
be the "Server" or "Guest OS" optimized versions of Linux.<br /><wbr>
<br /><wbr>
--- Tony <br /><wbr>
<br /><wbr>
</p>
